packages`, `requires`, or URL fields unless the PR clearly needs them.\n./skills/review-library-bulk-update/SKILL.md:35:     - matching `index.json` changes to `metadata-version`, `tested-versions`, and exact-version artifact URLs\n./skills/review-library-bulk-update/SKILL.md:57:   - Confirm the new versions were added under the correct `metadata-version` entry.\n./skills/review-library-bulk-update/SKILL.md:60:   - For pre-release promotions, confirm `metadata-version` moved from the matching pre-release to the corresponding full release, old pre-release values were removed from `tested-versions`, and any `test-version` references were updated only when they pointed at the promoted test directory.\n./skills/review-library-bulk-update/SKILL.md:65:   - For pre-release promotions, verify the `source-code-url`, `test-code-url`, and `documentation-url` values were rendered from the old version to the promoted `metadata-version` or otherwise corrected to an exact-version URL. Do not accept stale URLs that still point at the old pre-release.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:43:- A directory tree under `metadata/<groupId>/<artifactId>/<metadata-version>/` containing JSON files in the format described by GraalVM's [Native Image Manual Configuration](https://www.graalvm.org/latest/reference-manual/native-image/dynamic-features/Reflection/#manual-configuration) reference.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:46:- A `stats/<groupId>/<artifactId>/<metadata-version>/stats.json` mirror of per-version metrics (dynamic-access call sites, coverage, lines of code, dependency information).\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:52:- Validation of `index.json` schema and `metadata-version`/`tested-versions` integrity.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:155:<groupId>/<artifactId>/<metadata-version>/\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:161:**2. `<groupId>/<artifactId>/index.json`** — one per supported artifact, schema [metadata-library-index-schema-v2.1.0.json](../metadata/schemas/metadata-library-index-schema-v2.1.0.json). It is a JSON **array** of entries. Metadata entries require `metadata-version`, `tested-versions`, and `allowed-packages`, with optional `default-for` (Java regex), `latest: true`, `override: true`, `requires: [\"<group>:<artifact>\", …]`, `test-version`, `skipped-versions`, `language`, and the four URL fields. An index can alternatively contain a single `not-for-native-image: true` marker with a reason. Plugin-relevant fields are the first six.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:163:The schema follows semver, and **minor- and patch-version bumps** (e.g., `v2.1.0` → `v2.1.1` or `v2.1.x` → `v2.2.0`) are guaranteed to be backward-compatible with native-build-tools. Minor bumps add new optional fields or non-plugin index formats used by the website, the test harness, or future tooling (`requires`, `test-version`, `skipped-versions`, `language`, `source-code-url`, `test-code-url`, `documentation-url`, `repository-url`, `not-for-native-image`); patch bumps refine validation of those same auxiliary fields and formats. The plugin reads only the six fields enumerated above, so an older native-build-tools release continues to resolve metadata correctly against any newer minor or patch version of the schema. Only a **major-version bump** can break the contract, which NFR-4 forbids — schema changes are additive only.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:165:**3. `<groupId>/<artifactId>/<metadata-version>/reachability-metadata.json`** — the only file the plugin loads at native-image time. Schema [reachability-metadata-schema-v1.2.0.json](../metadata/schemas/reachability-metadata-schema-v1.2.0.json) (a vendored copy of the upstream GraalVM schema), with top-level keys `reflection`, `jni`, `resources`, `bundles`, `serialization`, and `foreignCalls`. Every entry must carry a `condition.typeReachable` clause (FR-M-2) so the plugin can rely on conditional registration. The legacy split-config layout (`reflect-config.json`, `jni-config.json`, …) is no longer present.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:169:1. `v ∈ tested-versions` → use that entry's `metadata-version` directory directly.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:178:    Tested -- yes --> UseTested[\"Use that entry's<br/><code>metadata-version/</code>\"]\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:180:    DefaultFor -- yes --> UseDefault[\"Use that entry's<br/><code>metadata-version/</code>\"]\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:184:    Latest -- yes --> UseLatest[\"Use that entry's<br/><code>metadata-version/</code>\"]\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:212:- **FR-T-2** Tests live under `tests/src/<group>/<artifact>/<version>` unless an `index.json` entry sets `test-version` to share a suite across versions.\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:2469:            return entry.get(\"test-version\") or entry.get(\"metadata-version\")\n./docs/support/index.html:586:          if (entry[\"metadata-version\"]) {\n./docs/support/index.html:587:            versions.add(entry[\"metadata-version\"]);\n./docs/support/index.html:649:            metadataValue(\"Latest metadata\", latest[\"metadata-version\"]),\n./docs/support/index.html:666:            metadataValue(\"Metadata version\", latest[\"metadata-version\"]),\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/stats/LibraryStatsModels.java:27: * Strongly-typed models for repository-aggregated and metadata-version-local library stats JSON payloads.\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:166:- `stats/<groupId>/<artifactId>/<metadata-version>/stats.json`\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:167:- One file per metadata-version directory\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:168:- Each local file contains the `versions` array for that metadata-version only\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:179:- Workflow scripts write execution metrics under `stats/<groupId>/<artifactId>/<metadata-version>/execution-metrics.json`.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:16:- Expect compile-focused changes plus the normal generated support files for the newly tested version: test source updates, imports, renamed APIs, dependency adjustments, a new metadata-version directory, stats, and metada